Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.09,0:00:18.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ruhenheim...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.38,0:00:21.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.07,0:01:54.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it, Ludwig!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.32,0:01:57.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this dog barking at?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.88,0:02:03.01,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(213,200)\pos(357,351)}Ruhenheim
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.12,0:02:03.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That bike is broken again?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.66,0:02:07.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, the chain keeps coming off.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.75,0:02:11.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I should have figured it was in the dumpster for a reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.04,0:02:16.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't look like trash to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.01,0:02:20.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whenever I ride this, everybody says, "Look!\NLook at the moving pile of trash!"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.51,0:02:24.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That trash is riding some trash...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.64,0:02:26.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.73,0:02:29.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a wonderful 5-speed supercycle.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.57,0:02:37.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here, let's try fixing it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.15,0:02:40.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like you have a customer.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.12,0:02:46.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's right. I received a call earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.50,0:02:50.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, are you the one who reserved a room...?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.25,0:02:53.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. My name is Lunge.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.34,0:02:56.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Mr. Lunge.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.09,0:02:58.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.92,0:03:02.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad there was a room available on such short notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.39,0:03:05.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, the rooms are always empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.76,0:03:08.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is still the off-season.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.68,0:03:11.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It feels like it's the off-season all year long.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.81,0:03:16.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only other people staying here\Nare that elderly couple over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.78,0:03:19.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Her husband injured his legs...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.32,0:03:22.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...so it seems that they have difficulties traveling.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.99,0:03:27.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take your bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.33,0:03:29.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please do, Wim.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.58,0:03:31.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's in room 302.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.04,0:03:35.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How is the view from that room?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.13,0:03:39.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it has the best view in the building.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.60,0:03:48.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll put your bag here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.06,0:03:50.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't look like trash to me, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.94,0:03:55.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it looked like an excellent bike.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.28,0:04:01.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Lunge of the BKA!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.40,0:04:04.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you at a branch office all the\Nway out in a country town like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.28,0:04:09.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was wondering how much backup\Nyou could request out here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.49,0:04:11.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Request? Backup?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.91,0:04:17.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, if we contact state headquarters, we can get\Na lot of reinforcements in as little as an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.71,0:04:22.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I don't think anything big like that would\Nhappen in a country town like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.93,0:04:27.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should check everyone who\Ncomes into town starting now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.77,0:04:33.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Before anything terrible happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.90,0:04:36.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Great! Keep going!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.77,0:04:38.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice run!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.11,0:04:39.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go faster!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.61,0:04:40.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Change gear!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.78,0:04:47.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ouch...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.33,0:04:50.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's up, trash?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.95,0:04:53.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That trash is still moving?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.37,0:04:56.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This trash is painful to look at!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.83,0:04:57.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.88,0:04:59.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.67,0:05:02.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stupid trash!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.09,0:05:05.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're just trash!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.52,0:05:13.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.15,0:05:21.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.90,0:05:24.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you traveling by yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.36,0:05:26.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.32,0:05:27.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here for work?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.74,0:05:29.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, private business.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.53,0:05:30.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.53,0:05:32.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you lonely by yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.25,0:05:35.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm used to jt.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.46,0:05:37.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have a family?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.79,0:05:38.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I have one.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.79,0:05:40.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My daughter even has a son now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.09,0:05:43.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, a grandson!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.88,0:05:46.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grandsons are great.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.13,0:05:50.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They care about us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.89,0:05:55.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look! I was writing a postcard to my grandson just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.64,0:05:57.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Letters are nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.94,0:06:02.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In letters, you can write things you can't say face to face.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.90,0:06:05.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you try writing one as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.40,0:06:08.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A letter to my grandson...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.53,0:06:11.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I don't even know what to write...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.87,0:06:14.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anything will do.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.58,0:06:18.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I could draw...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.79,0:06:23.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.25,0:06:25.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can I stay here for the night?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.71,0:06:27.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.97,0:06:30.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's great!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.34,0:06:33.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was enjoying a relaxing picnic...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.10,0:06:35.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I got lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.43,0:06:37.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that I've finally arrived in town...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.94,0:06:40.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it's already late.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.69,0:06:43.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I really appreciate this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.20,0:06:57.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like nobody's getting off at this town.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.25,0:07:06.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A gunshot?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.22,0:07:11.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't hear any gunshots.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.30,0:07:15.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I swear I heard it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.56,0:07:18.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No one in this town has a gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.85,0:07:22.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If anyone did, it'd be that drunk out back.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.31,0:07:25.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If he shot it out from the back of the house.\Nit'd sound much louder.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.98,0:07:30.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, that drunk couldn't hit anything, even if he tried.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.11,0:07:32.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it! I lost again!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.16,0:07:38.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I lost again because you jinxed me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.25,0:07:39.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.00,0:07:39.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.62,0:07:41.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not my fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.08,0:07:43.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you just stop trying to win the lottery already?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.21,0:07:49.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ludwig!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.59,0:07:52.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ludwig!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.26,0:07:56.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't find my Ludwig anywhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.76,0:07:59.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You heard that gunshot just now, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.31,0:08:02.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What if my Ludwig was...!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.98,0:08:04.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What if my baby was...!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.23,0:08:07.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please calm down, Mrs. Hillman.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.15,0:08:09.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There weren't any gunshots.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.23,0:08:10.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.94,0:08:12.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.82,0:08:17.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, this woman's dog has gone missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.28,0:08:18.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.04,0:08:19.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's always a worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.37,0:08:22.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, let's call the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.71,0:08:24.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I already reported it to the police!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.92,0:08:26.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you can't count on that man!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.75,0:08:29.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though he's an officer, he's totally unreliable!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.46,0:08:31.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How could you rely on an officer who hates dogs?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.55,0:08:34.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you like me to go look for him?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.22,0:08:37.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure, Mr. Neumaier?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.76,0:08:38.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.60,0:08:41.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was going to wander around town anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.31,0:08:47.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I know Mrs. Hillman's dog quite well.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.73,0:08:50.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're talking about that stupid\Nmutt that never shuts up, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.73,0:08:52.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.49,0:08:54.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you seen him?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.15,0:08:55.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I haven't.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.91,0:08:58.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.53,0:08:59.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, one more thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.95,0:09:04.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you seen any unfamiliar or suspicious\Ncharacters around town lately?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.00,0:09:05.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I have.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.33,0:09:07.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.01,0:09:13.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A dog?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.51,0:09:16.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you were going to stay here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.68,0:09:17.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.72,0:09:20.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm staying at the Versteck Hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.47,0:09:24.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Man, he takes all of my customers.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.85,0:09:28.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means nobody is staying at this hotel?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.81,0:09:30.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.19,0:09:32.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to him, I lead a quiet life.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.73,0:09:37.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I'd know right away\Nif that noisy dog was around.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.36,0:09:39.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you heard him bark today?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.83,0:09:42.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I haven't.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.04,0:09:43.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But maybe...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.79,0:09:46.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You heard what sounded like a gunshot, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.75,0:09:51.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe some degenerate got fed up and shot him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.80,0:10:03.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, hello. Umm...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.89,0:10:06.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Lunge, Mr. Neumaier.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.10,0:10:07.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Mr. Lunge.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.35,0:10:08.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you headed?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.77,0:10:10.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm looking for the dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.19,0:10:12.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.77,0:10:15.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you find any clues?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.40,0:10:16.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.36,0:10:20.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then let's keep looking.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.42,0:10:34.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alcohol!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.34,0:10:35.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get me some alcohol!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.51,0:10:37.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, Dad! You can't have any more!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.84,0:10:40.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up and buy me some alcohol!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.30,0:10:41.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have any money!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.89,0:10:44.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know you got some money working at the hotel!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.49,0:11:01.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I can buy a bottle...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.16,0:11:02.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wim.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.49,0:11:04.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.70,0:11:07.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You earned that money.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.92,0:11:13.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like you had another rough day.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.54,0:11:16.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, come on. Let's go back to my hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.65,0:11:32.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.94,0:11:37.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not many people eat with such enthusiasm.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.74,0:11:38.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.65,0:11:40.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But good food is delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.49,0:11:43.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to get all worked up over a sausage.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.16,0:11:46.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is how I look when I eat something delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.79,0:11:49.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a nice town.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.29,0:11:51.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's quiet and has good food.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.08,0:11:53.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.75,0:11:57.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to hurry up and get out of this boring town.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.00,0:12:01.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope a wonderful person will show up one\Nday and take me away from this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.88,0:12:04.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Has a wonderful person stopped by lately?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.10,0:12:05.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.56,0:12:08.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm getting sick of seeing the same old faces every day!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.89,0:12:11.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, about the dog...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.02,0:12:15.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I've taken that dog for a walk before.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.61,0:12:16.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A walk?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.98,0:12:21.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When Mrs. Hillman had a cold, I helped\Nher out by walking the dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.74,0:12:26.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I gave it one of our Eisbein bones\Nfrom the deli, it wouldn't let it go!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.83,0:12:30.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then he wouldn't stop pulling!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.12,0:12:31.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How far did you guys go?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.42,0:12:37.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Lunge!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.59,0:12:41.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A terrible thing happened, just like you said.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.59,0:12:43.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.63,0:12:45.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A dog has gone missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.18,0:12:48.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you hear any gunshots?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.51,0:12:51.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that wasn't a gunshot.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.48,0:12:54.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A car broke down on the highway.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.15,0:12:57.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must've heard the engine backfiring.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.11,0:13:00.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You won't hear any gunshots in this town.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.69,0:13:01.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.88,0:13:22.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't want to scare me, if you\Nknow what's good for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.76,0:13:29.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.06,0:13:33.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ludwig.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.10,0:13:36.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've caused so much trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.69,0:13:39.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you remembered you buried that bone here, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.70,0:13:48.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well hello, Mr. Lunge.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.99,0:13:53.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like we've arrived at the same\Nplace through different clues.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.58,0:13:57.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing in this town?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.33,0:14:00.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.38,0:14:02.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're a detective, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.67,0:14:05.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.09,0:14:07.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You just have that kind of air about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.55,0:14:09.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm on vacation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.68,0:14:13.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those eyes don't say you're on vacation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.89,0:14:16.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was in Prague until recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.02,0:14:22.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There, I heard information about a\Nman involved in a certain incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.48,0:14:25.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A tall man carrying a large bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.20,0:14:29.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He had a social, friendly smile.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.28,0:14:31.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The color of his hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.12,0:14:38.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You match the description of the\Nman in my data, Mr. Neumaier.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.21,0:14:43.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No... Mr. Grimmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.72,0:14:48.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you here in this town?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.93,0:14:56.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems that we really did arrive at the\Nsame place through different clues.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.98,0:14:58.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.73,0:15:04.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think we can stop it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.48,0:15:09.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The terrible massacre that is going\Nto happen in this town...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.38,0:15:28.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you're checking the lottery numbers again?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.84,0:15:32.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not going to say anything to your husband\Nwho's about to spend all day sweating?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.22,0:15:34.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You talk like you make a lot of money.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.39,0:15:35.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.89,0:15:38.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our life will be a total disaster if we\Ndon't win the lottery or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.77,0:15:40.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you've got a problem with that, go make more money!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.98,0:15:43.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Honey!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.94,0:15:45.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up! What do you want?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.61,0:15:47.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Honey...!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.19,0:15:49.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you want, I said!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.95,0:15:51.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.20,0:15:52.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You won what?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.95,0:15:55.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I... I won the lottery...!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.91,0:15:57.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give it back!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.16,0:15:59.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where did you put my bike?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.87,0:16:01.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please give it back!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.42,0:16:03.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.29,0:16:05.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't know about any bikes, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.29,0:16:07.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We did throw away some trash, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.80,0:16:09.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You threw it away?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.80,0:16:13.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, we threw it into the vampire's\Nmansion on the western hill.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.43,0:16:17.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Vampire...?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.43,0:16:20.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you want it back, go get it yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.31,0:16:22.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You better watch out, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.48,0:16:24.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stupid trash!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.91,0:16:44.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Honey...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.04,0:16:46.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody came by, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.04,0:16:47.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,N-No...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.30,0:16:49.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't forget to put the chain on.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.72,0:16:51.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.47,0:16:52.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.76,0:16:55.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You sure you didn't get the numbers wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.64,0:16:57.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I... I checked them over and over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.68,0:17:00.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-We really did win.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.64,0:17:03.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Twenty million marks...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.56,0:17:05.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What should we do, dear...?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.90,0:17:08.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I went to the next town over.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.03,0:17:12.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,D-Dear! These are...!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.28,0:17:15.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just in case.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.03,0:17:18.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not safe to have such a large sum\Nof money without any protection.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.53,0:17:23.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if nobody finds out about it, we won't need these.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.12,0:17:24.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.25,0:17:26.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.50,0:17:30.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody knows the numbers you\Npicked for the lottery, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.51,0:17:33.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Well, the truth is...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.34,0:17:35.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-When I bought that ticket...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.84,0:17:38.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The usual.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.93,0:17:40.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.47,0:17:45.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It sure is hard to win, isn't it, Mrs. Hennich?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.19,0:17:47.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, hello, Mr. Konrad.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.40,0:17:51.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your husband was throwing a fit about\Nhow addicted you are to the lottery.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.65,0:17:56.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, feel free to use my birthday if you wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.78,0:18:01.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,March 2, 1945.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.24,0:18:03.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It works pretty well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.62,0:18:08.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've won big twice at the track.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.54,0:18:10.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, yes. Thank you for your concern.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.50,0:18:16.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,D-Don't tell me you used Konrad's birthday...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.72,0:18:22.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l-lf he reads the newspaper and sees the numbers...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.60,0:18:27.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But he doesn't know that you actually\Nused those numbers, does he?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.35,0:18:28.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.65,0:18:31.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe the rumors have spread across town already.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.40,0:18:32.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,N-Now that you mention it...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.78,0:18:33.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.78,0:18:38.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I stopped by the general store to\Nbuy some cigarettes on the way home...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.03,0:18:42.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the girl from the sausage store was looking at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.54,0:18:45.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.83,0:18:46.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It happened to me, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.62,0:18:49.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I went to take out the trash just now...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.46,0:18:51.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the drunk in back of our house...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.79,0:18:54.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was staring at me!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.59,0:18:58.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows what will happen if he hears\Nabout us having so much money!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.93,0:18:59.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.80,0:19:00.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.34,0:19:04.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen! We have to protect ourselves now!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.24,0:19:20.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The vampire's mansion...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.17,0:19:40.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l-lt's dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.82,0:20:00.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone's here!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.45,0:20:08.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From the look of things...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.08,0:20:12.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He doesn't seem to have been here recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.29,0:20:15.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're all unfinished.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.17,0:20:16.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does it mean that he stopped drawing them?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.96,0:20:20.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or that he couldn't continue to draw anymore?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.64,0:20:27.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, if it isn't Wim.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.06,0:20:31.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Neumaier?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.73,0:20:32.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Lunge?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.69,0:20:35.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.44,0:20:36.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.19,0:20:37.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,M-My bike...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.61,0:20:40.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Some of my friends said they threw my bike in here, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.99,0:20:44.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it looks like your friends played a trick on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.45,0:20:49.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're looking for your bike, I saw it in the thicket\Nnear the entrance to the mountain path.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.54,0:20:53.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.58,0:20:57.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like that cat was shot with a submachine gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.88,0:20:59.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, they're already...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.88,0:21:02.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, they're already nearby.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.05,0:21:08.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.85,0:21:12.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A drawing of twins?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.19,0:21:13.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.31,0:21:17.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This one, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.19,0:21:20.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And another one.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.39,0:21:22.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And another...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.99,0:21:24.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And another...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.66,0:21:26.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And another...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.53,0:21:29.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And another...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.87,0:21:32.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're about ten years old here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.17,0:21:36.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I was in charge of Tenma's case...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.96,0:21:39.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,those twins were about ten years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.92,0:21:42.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All of these seem to have been drawn around that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.05,0:21:46.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just how many pictures did he draw?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.51,0:21:51.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how many he drew...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.10,0:21:53.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he was never satisfied.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.90,0:22:00.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Man, there are so many vines this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.15,0:22:04.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm worried about how many cowberries\Nwe'll be able to harvest this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.00,0:22:18.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you're an unfamiliar face.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.93,0:22:31.10,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(199,471)}Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.10,0:22:44.53,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(199,475)}Cherish what you know is true in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.10,0:22:44.53,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(196,21)}Ima kono sekai de wakaru koto mitsumete
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.53,0:22:47.49,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(182,472)}Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.49,0:23:01.17,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(198,472)}Please believe in the kindness of your eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.49,0:23:01.17,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(199,21)}Anata no hitomi no yasashisa wo shinjite
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.77,0:23:26.03,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(196,473)}Make it home to your land of harmony
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.03,0:23:34.45,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(195,473)}Make it home to your land of purity
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.45,0:23:36.91,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,246)\pos(187,472)}Make it home
